  "title": "Admin Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title:</strong> Admin Assistant (Warehouse Office)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job description :</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Handles critical administrative tasks focused on accurately managing stock movements — including delivery orders and stock returns — using both computer systems and Excel. This role demands exceptional attention to detail, swift and accurate data entry, and the ability to work efficiently under tight deadlines.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· <strong>Stock Documentation &amp; Data Entry</strong></p>\n<p>o Accurately update delivery orders, stock returns, and all warehouse-related transactions in the computer system and Excel.</p>\n<p>o Input in/out inventory with precision, ensuring timely and error-free entries</p>\n<p>o Assist with picking lists, packing lists, internal transfers, and returns documentation</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>·  <strong>Warehouse System Management</strong></p>\n<p>· Operate and maintain the warehouse management or ERP system to track inventory movements efficiently</p>\n<p>· ensuring system records reconcile with physical counts.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>·  <strong>Recordkeeping &amp; Filing</strong></p>\n<p>· Establish and maintain a neat, reliable filing system for all warehouse documents and data entries.</p>\n<p>· Assist in generating reports and providing regular status updates to internal stakeholders</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Collaborative Support</strong></p>\n<p>· Liaise with internal departments—logistics, purchasing, sales—to resolve discrepancies and update order statuses</p>\n<p>· Support warehouse staff during peak periods or staff absences; assist pickers/receivers when needed</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>General Administrative Duties</strong></p>\n<p>· Manage deliveries and returns or new purchases documentations accurately.</p>\n<p>· Provide ad-hoc clerical support as assigned.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications &amp; Skills</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Educational Background</strong></p>\n<p>o Minimum: GCE O‑Levels, NITEC, or equivalent.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· <strong>Technical Proficiency</strong></p>\n<p>o Strong in Microsoft Excel (e.g., formulas, pivot tables) and other Office tools.</p>\n<p>o Familiarity with ERP or warehouse management systems preferred</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· <strong>Core Competencies</strong></p>\n<p>o Exceptional attention to detail, ensuring high accuracy in data entry and documentation</p>\n<p>o Fast and efficient in managing high-volume, repetitive tasks.</p>\n<p>o Excellent time management and ability to meet tight deadlines</p>",
